## IT Disaster Recovery Messaging

### Pain Points
- Lack of confidence in the ability to recover from a major incident and meet application/service RTOs
- Time-consuming and ineffective testing that doesn't reflect real incidents
- Complex regulatory compliance reporting — manually intensive and error prone
- Disjointed processes and high risk of human error from manual-intensive recovery methods
- Isolated and siloed DevOps, SRE, and tech operations teams

### Value Props / Benefits
- Gain confidence and recover faster with automated runbooks — regardless of application deployment (cloud native, hybrid, multi-cloud)
- Create repeatable recovery plans for announced and unannounced testing with templated runbooks
- Ensure governance, simplify regulatory reporting, and demonstrate controls with the auto-generated audit log
- Automate and streamline recovery processes to increase efficiency and reduce human error
- Single source of execution and visibility for recovery across siloed teams with integrations to Slack, MS Teams, Zoom

### Proof Points
- 50% reduction in execution time
- 70% less manual effort and time in test preparation and execution
- Reduce testing time from 12 weeks to 2
- 60% increase in audit efficiency
- 300% improvement in resilience efficiency

