## Cyber Recovery Messaging

### Pain Points
- Cyber attacks are more complex and unpredictable than traditional ITDR outages
- Difficult to know if the traditional failover site has been affected or the degree of infection/blast radius
- Lack of board and business confidence in the ability to recover quickly
- Difficult to test cyber recovery without taking down production applications
- Complex and time-consuming regulatory compliance reporting
- Disjointed processes leading to human error
- Isolated and siloed teams (DevOps, SREs, Tech Ops)
- High availability architectures (containers, microservices) increase complexity

### Value Props / Benefits
- Reduce complexity and unpredictability with the Cutover platform — combine human decision making and automated tasks
- Gain confidence with dynamic runbooks that bring order to the chaos
- Simplify testing and create repeatable, templated runbooks from well-defined recovery plans
- Auto-generated audit log simplifies regulatory reporting
- Real-time dashboards provide stakeholders instant visibility to recovery progress
- Dynamic runbooks and built-in logic enable orchestration to adapt as new information comes to light

### Proof Points
- 50% reduction in execution time
- 70% less time in test preparation and execution
- 60% increase in audit efficiency
- 300% improvement in resilience efficiency
- 309% ROI on average for Cutover customers

