## Cutover Resilience Messaging (Broader)

### Value Statements
- **Rehearse and recover from total or partial loss** — perform large-scale testing or test specific business applications with repeatable runbooks all in one place
- **Achieve OPEX savings** — reduce event planning and execution by up to 80%; eliminate configuration drift with real-time visibility
- **Gain financial services regulatory compliance** — meet existing and upcoming financial services regulatory requirements with executable runbooks, immutable audit trail, and real-time reporting
- **Connect teams and technology** — take the risk and cost out of SRE and Tech Ops; keep stakeholders and DR teams in sync

### Use Cases
1. Major incident management
2. IT disaster recovery
3. Cloud disaster recovery
4. Cyber resilience
5. IT system health checks

### Key Features
| Feature | Key Attributes |
|---|---|
| Dynamic, Automated Runbooks | Library of templated runbooks; one centralized workspace; ability to link runbooks; node map for dependencies; automated recovery platform integrating across the recovery stack |
| Reporting, Analytics, Dashboards & Audit Log | Indelible audit trails; real-time dashboards; post-analysis dashboard; automated post-incident review; comprehensive labelled data |
| Integration Suite | Pre-built integrations (outbound API); custom integration (outbound API); Developer Portal (inbound API) |

### Words to Avoid (Resilience)
- Cloud/IT DR: Data Backup; DR as a Service; SOAP; hyperautomation; Intelligent Automation; Operational Resilience; Business Continuity
- Cyber Resilience: Cybersecurity (protect against/avoid threats); penetration testing; Incident response (system); SOAR; SIEM
- System Health: "health checks"

