## Cutover Respond Messaging

### Solution Positioning
> Cutover Respond offers a solution to streamline and enable automation and AI agents for the entire incident management lifecycle. Through automated workflows, a task-based model, AI agent integration, centralized communication, and real-time visibility, Respond facilitates a faster and more coordinated approach, ultimately reducing mean time to resolution (MTTR).

### Overarching Value Proposition
**Cutover Respond helps you meaningfully reduce MTTR.**

### Five Value Pillars
| Pillar | What it means |
|---|---|
| Rapid mobilization | Rapid, automated team mobilization reduces time to engage Resolvers. Removes manual effort in determining who is involved. MIMs focus on directing the response, not admin work |
| Seamless visibility and tracking of work (task-based model) | Real-time task tracking outside of chat keeps everyone aligned and accountable. Reduces missed steps and errors, especially under stress |
| Self-serve stakeholder visibility and comms (without interrupting the technical team) | Self-serve, real-time updates cut down on interruptions. Shared visibility builds trust and keeps all parties aligned without extra effort from the MIM or resolvers |
| Less toil and quicker resolution through AI agents and automation | Superior automation handles routine tasks freeing teams to focus on high-value work. AI agents surface actionable insights for human-in-the-loop interpretation |
| Automated post-incident review and comprehensive labelled data for learning | Automatic capture of entire incident data. Simplified report generation and auditing saves hours post-incident |

### Pain Points Addressed
- "It takes too long to find and reach the right people."
- "We lose track of who's doing what under pressure in the chat channels."
- "I get bombarded with status requests when I'm trying to manage the incident."
- "Too much of my time is spent on repetitive tasks that could be automated."
- "Post-mortems take forever to write up."
- "We keep making the same mistakes because lessons learned don't get shared or actioned."

### Target Personas for Respond
- People who own ITIL processes of Incident, Problem, and Change
- Major Incident Managers (MIMs)
- Resolvers
- Executives / CIO
- **Primary verticals:** FSIs and other verticals that use ServiceNow SOW+MIM

### Competitive Context (Respond)
- Primary competitor: ServiceNow Service Operations Workspace and MIM Module

